	<Summary>The Long Way Home

While enjoying a pint of Murphy's "best deal", Sloan began feeling disoriented which caused a wave of panic to quickly set in and he raced toward the exit.

What was happening? Was he drugged? Was it real or a hallucination?

Once outside, he met a strange man who went by the name of Master Thoth. Their conversation was cut short by another member of the PSTF, Leo Elaiam, who revealed he also took the same transformative formula that turned Gordon, aka Cannonball, into a meta-human!

Talk about bad timing!

Despite his handicap, Sloan bested Leo with the help of Thoth and left him to bleed out. Now, Sloan wanders the streets of Paradise in his deranged state with his new friend who appears to be quite unhinged, himself.

What kind of trouble will these two get into?</Summary>
